3.4. Phenotyping analysis by SNPeffect

Alterations in the phenotypic properties of the 12 high-risk variants were assessed by SNPeffect 4.0 by considering the aggregation propensity, amyloid forming tendency, chaperon binding propensity and changes in the stability ( Table 2 ). Among them, 11 variants (L23P, I52T, M53R/T, G54D, R71T, L76P, V113F, Y122D, D146G, P150A and F180C) were unaffected with dTANGO scores of between -26.31 and 32.00 in the aggregation prone regions.

Table 2 . Phenotypic characterization of selected mutants by the SNPeffect.
